769. J Health Econ. 2002 May;21(3):397-403. doi: 10.1016/s0167-6296(01)00136-9.

A proposal to solve the comparability problem in cost-utility analysis.

Bleichrodt H(1), Herrero C, Pinto JL.

Author information:
(1)iMTA/iBMG, Erasmus University, Rotterdam, The Netherlands. 
bleichrodt@bmg.eur.nl

In cost-utility analysis it is assumed that health state valuations are directly 
comparable across individuals. Instead, health state valuations may be relative 
and related to people's expectations and abilities. Then health state valuations 
are not fully comparable across people and, consequently, cost utility analysis 
cannot be applied in full. The present paper analyzes this comparability problem 
and proposes a method to solve it.

